@startmindmap
* Unified Risk Layer for DeFi
** Response-path frictions
*** On-chain governance\nslow, human consensus, not scalable
*** Delegated operators\nefficient but trust-based
*** On-chain controllers\nreal-time but narrow data
** The risk layer
*** sits above the oracle network
*** ingests diverse signals\nliquidity, volatility, macro, credit
*** defines thresholds + responses
*** outputs
**** risk-managed pricing
**** risk-managed responses\ncircuit breakers, param changes
** Aave's journey
*** 2020 on-chain governance
*** 2023 manual risk stewards
*** 2024 first-gen risk oracles
*** black-box limitation\nopaque, silent failure, manipulable
** Protocol-owned infra (CRE)
*** credibly neutral, node-validated
*** off-chain workflow owned by protocol
*** transparent to team + auditors
** Pendle PT use case
*** PT = zero-coupon bond, fixed maturity
*** linear discount = unused efficiency
*** time-varying risk profile
**** volatile early, deterministic late
*** optimize discount + liquidation params
*** inputs: AMM price + parameter registry
*** CRE writes via Llama Guard oracle
@endmindmap
